Del Rio, Tennessee

An [unincorporated community](/Unincorporated_area) nestled within [Cocke County](/Cocke_County,_Tennessee), [Tennessee](/Tennessee), United States, Del Rio exists as a geographical designation rather than a formally chartered municipality. While it may lack the official trappings of a [census-designated place](/Census-designated_place), its presence is marked by a distinct [ZIP Code Tabulation Area](/ZIP_Code_Tabulation_Area) (ZCTA) for the [ZIP Code](/ZIP_Code) 37727. According to the rather outdated metrics of the [2000 census](/United_States_Census,_2000), this area registered a population of 2,138 souls, a number that likely shifts with the same indifferent rhythm as the nearby river.

